  "texts": [
    "In common with other clinical use cases, PHM requires models to be explainable to clinicians.",
    "The main contributions of this research can be summarized as follows:",
    "Developing a simple and effective approach to incorporating an increased data scope, including introducing a novel (to our knowledge) methodology for incorporating complete sets of lab test values into an FEMR and the addition of novel features associated with wider determinants of health.",
    "Demonstrating the effectiveness of pre-trained code embeddings to enhance predictive performance for key PHM outcomes where limited data is available, both within and across subpopulations. 3.",
    "Investigating whether SHAP could be deployed to improve the explainability of FEMRs to enable clinicians to interrogate the features contributing to the prediction of future outcomes for patients and cohorts."
